Antennae (
Fig. 15
) slender, 0.48 times as long as body, length ratio of antennomeres I–XI equal to 100: 71: 86: 86: 129: 114: 114: 114: 100: 100: 143. Pronotum (
Fig. 10
) quadratic, as wide as long, widest in anterior third. Surface weakly constricted before base, between constriction and posterior margin low thin ridge. Anterior margin nearly straight, thinly bordered, anterior half of lateral margins almost parallel, straight, posterior half convergent.
